title: Shakespearean Small Language Model
description: Developing a Shakespearean sentence completion model using LSTM and TensorFlow Keras, training on compiled text. Preprocessed Shakespearean text by cleaning, tokenizing, and vectorizing data, ensuring compatibility with framework. Led model experimentation efforts, refining preprocessing scripts and optimizing sentence parameters to enhance accuracy.

title: National Power Outage Duration Predictor
description: Conducted comprehensive data cleaning and preprocessing on U.S. power outage records (2000-2016), for suitable analysis. Built a multiclass classification model using a Random Forest Classifier to predict power outage severity (Short, Moderate, Long, Severe), leveraging an sklearn pipeline to streamline preprocessing and training, enhancing predictive accuracy.

title: Dexteria 2.0 App Reoptimization
description: Leading a team of designers, data analysts, and marketers to optimize Dexteria 2, a therapy game app, for stroke rehab. Analyzing app usage data and conducting user interviews with physical therapists to identify underutilized features and user pain points, enabling data-driven recommendations to improve appâ€™s features and usability for the stroke survivor market.

title: Meteorite Landing Analysis and Modeling
description: Analyzed a NASA Open Data Portal dataset on meteorite landings to pinpoint patterns in the locations of fallen meteorites. Utilized hypothesis testing to determine if the observed data from random samples aligns with the predicted distribution.

title: Song Recommendation System
description: Developed a Python-based song recommendation system based on the quantified similarity to a Taylor Swift song input. Implemented a search tool to input a term and find the total occurrences and number of Taylor Swift songs it appears in.
